.Dd March 23, 2018
.Dt VFS_UNMOUNTALL 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm vfs_unmountall
.Nd unmount all file systems
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/mount.h
.Ft void
.Fn vfs_unmountall "int halting"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
function,
run only at system shutdown,
unmounts all mounted file systems
from most recent to oldest
in order to avoid handling dependencies.
.Pp
If
.Fa halting
is set to 1,
.Nm
will disconnect but leave certain mount points, such as
.Xr devfs 5 ,
intact.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr boot 9
